   "source": [
    "# Application with new data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b6bc435e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This tutorial demonstrates how to pseudo-spatiotemporal analysis on BaristaSeq mouse visual cortex data using Pysodb and SpaceFlow.\n",
    "\n",
    "A reference paper can be found at https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-022-31739-w.\n",
    "\n",
    "This tutorial refers to the following tutorial at https://github.com/hongleir/SpaceFlow/blob/master/tutorials/seqfish_mouse_embryogenesis.ipynb. At the same time, the way of loadding data is modified by using Pysodb."
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6365cf7d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Import packages and set configurations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "e0c21753",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Use the Python warnings module to filter and ignore any warnings that may occur in the program after this point.\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings(\"ignore\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "ada79d57",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import several python packages commonly used in data analysis and visualization.\n",
    "# numpy (imported as np) is a package for numerical computing with arrays.\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "# scanpy (imported as sc) is a package for single-cell RNA sequencing analysis.\n",
    "import scanpy as sc\n",
    "# matplotlib.pyplot (imported as plt) is a package for data visualization.\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "# seaborn (imported as sns) is a package for statistical data visualization, providing high-level interfaces for creating informative and attractive visualizations.\n",
    "import seaborn as sns"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "4690bf6a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# from SpaceFlow package import SpaceFlow module\n",
    "from SpaceFlow import SpaceFlow"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "045e600b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Imports a palettable package\n",
    "import palettable\n",
    "# Create three variables with lists of colors for categorical visualizations and biotechnology-related visualizations, respectively.\n",
    "cmp_pspace = palettable.cartocolors.diverging.TealRose_7.mpl_colormap\n",
    "cmp_domain = palettable.cartocolors.qualitative.Pastel_10.mpl_colors\n",
    "cmp_ct = palettable.cartocolors.qualitative.Safe_10.mpl_colors"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e76a0974",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Streamline development of loading spatial data with Pysodb"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "0629f64f-7408-42de-8891-0eba9e78a7d4",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import pysodb package\n",
    "# Pysodb is a Python package that provides a set of tools for working with SODB databases. \n",
    "# SODB is a format used to store data in memory-mapped files for efficient access and querying. \n",
    "# This package allows users to interact with SODB files using Python.\n",
    "import pysodb"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "dfab1be2-0ef5-48ea-85b1-fc0d86971237",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize the sodb object\n",
    "sodb = pysodb.SODB()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "bfaf697a-19a8-4a44-80d7-cc700a4bd011",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "load experiment[Slice_1] in dataset[Sun2021Integrating]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Define names of the dataset_name and experiment_name\n",
    "dataset_name = 'Sun2021Integrating'\n",
    "experiment_name = 'Slice_1'\n",
    "# Load a specific experiment\n",
    "# It takes two arguments: the name of the dataset and the name of the experiment to load.\n",
    "# Two arguments are available at https://gene.ai.tencent.com/SpatialOmics/.\n",
    "#%%time\n",
    "adata = sodb.load_experiment(dataset_name,experiment_name)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "a5889d32",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Remove cells belong to the layers 'outside_VISp' and 'VISp'\n",
    "adata = adata[adata.obs['layer']!='outside_VISp']\n",
    "adata = adata[adata.obs['layer']!='VISp']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "3cdfb359",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Filter out genes\n",
    "sc.pp.filter_genes(adata, min_cells=3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "attachments": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a685c4f4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Perform SpaceFlow for pseudo-spatiotemporal analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "66f7ba40",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create SpaceFlow Object\n",
    "#%%time\n",
    "#sf = SpaceFlow.SpaceFlow(adata=adata)    \n",
    "sf = SpaceFlow.SpaceFlow(\n",
    "    count_matrix=adata.X, \n",
    "    spatial_locs=adata.obsm['spatial'], \n",
    "    sample_names=adata.obs_names, \n",
    "    gene_names=adata.var_names\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "ab2884ff",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Preprocess data\n",
    "#%%time\n",
    "sf.preprocessing_data(n_top_genes=3000)"
   ]
  },

    "# Train a deep graph network model\n",
    "#%%time\n",
    "sf.train(\n",
    "    spatial_regularization_strength=0.1, \n",
    "    z_dim=50, \n",
    "    lr=1e-3, \n",
    "    epochs=1000, \n",
    "    max_patience=50, \n",
    "    min_stop=100, \n",
    "    random_seed=42, \n",
    "    gpu=0, \n",
    "    regularization_acceleration=True, \n",
    "    edge_subset_sz=1000000\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "138e7a86",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Performing pseudo-Spatiotemporal Map\n",
      "pseudo-Spatiotemporal Map(pSM) calculation complete, pSM values of cells or spots saved at ./pSM_values.tsv!\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Idenfify the spatiotemporal patterns through pseudo-Spatiotemporal Map (pSM)\n",
    "sf.pseudo_Spatiotemporal_Map(pSM_values_save_filepath=\"./pSM_values.tsv\", n_neighbors=20, resolution=1.0)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "91ecf746",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create a new column called 'pspace' from pSM values\n",
    "adata.obs['pspace'] = np.array(sf.pSM_values)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "d98304e3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Create a UMAP projection from SpaceFlow's embedding \n",
    "adata.obsm['embedding'] = sf.embedding\n",
    "sc.pp.neighbors(adata, n_neighbors=20, use_rep='embedding')\n",
    "sc.tl.umap(adata)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "46b7d1df",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Since this dataset contains 'depth_um' in obs, a iroot was set to be the cell with smallest depth_um. \n",
    "# For datasets without depth information, one can use the pseudo_Spatiotemporal_Map function\n",
    "# Here set the iroot according to \"depth_um\"\n",
    "\n",
    "# Select the root cell for trajectory inference based on its depth, by setting the index of the cell with the smallest 'depth_um' value as the root\n",
    "adata.uns['iroot'] = np.argmin(adata.obs['depth_um'])\n",
    "sc.tl.diffmap(adata)\n",
    "sc.tl.dpt(adata)  "
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "# Check whether the pseudo-spatiotemporal (dpt_pseudotime) from infer was correlated with their depth_um (depth_um)\n",
    "adata_use = adata\n",
    "g = sns.jointplot(x=\"depth_um\", y=\"dpt_pseudotime\", data=adata_use.obs,hue='layer',\n",
    "                  palette=list(adata_use.uns['layer_colors']),\n",
    "                  # kind=\"reg\", \n",
    "                  # truncate=False,\n",
    "                  # xlim=(0, 60), ylim=(0, 12),\n",
    "                  # color=\"m\", \n",
    "                  height=7)\n",
    "g.ax_joint.legend_.remove()\n",
